# eGymSystem.Backend Structure Rule

Apply in `eGymSystem.Backend` with this project layout:

- `eGymSystem.API` -> controllers, middleware, DI wiring only
- `eGymSystem.Application` -> CQRS commands/queries/handlers, validators, behaviors
- `eGymSystem.Domain` -> entities/enums/domain logic
- `eGymSystem.Infrastructure` -> EF Core, DbContext, configurations, migrations, external services
- `eGymSystem.Shared` -> shared DTOs/options/constants
- `eGymSystem.Tests` -> unit/integration tests

Generation rules:

- Keep controllers thin; call MediatR from API layer.
- New business flow: add `Command/Query` + `Handler` under `eGymSystem.Application/Modules/<Area>/...`.
- Validation belongs to Application (FluentValidation + pipeline behavior), not controller.
- Persistence mapping/config belongs to `eGymSystem.Infrastructure/Database/Configurations`.
- Reuse unified error shape (`ErrorDto`, exception handler path) instead of custom response style.
- Validation failures must return canonical envelope with stable error code + trace id.
- Keep auth flow compatible with existing JWT setup and fallback policy.
- Register new services via layer `DependencyInjection.cs`, not in random files.
- Do not create/edit files in `Market.Backend`; backend target is `eGymSystem.Backend` only.
- For scaffolding stage, expose full CRUD route surface with placeholder responses and no service/domain execution.
- Mirror `Market.Backend` folder/file naming patterns in `eGymSystem.Backend` whenever adding backend scaffold files (Controllers, Modules, DTO folders, Options, DI files, Common middleware/handlers, test layout).
